-- 2010-07-26T22:57:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/portugal-s-biggest-bank-may-acquire-25-stake-in-moza-banco-of-mozambique.html

          
          
             Banco Espirito Santo SA, Portugalâ€™s
biggest publicly traded bank by market value, signed a
memorandum of understanding to buy a 25 percent stake in Moza
Banco SA of Mozambique.  
 Moza Banco currently has about $54 million in assets, two
branches in Maputo and 53 employees, Lisbon-based Espirito Santo
said today in a regulatory filing. Its main business is
corporate banking, according to Espirito Santo.  
          
          


  


        